if a package name passed to `buildRelativePath()` instead of a fs path, it should return the package name as it.

```
buildRelativePath("app.module.ts", "./file.ts")
//returns  ../../file.ts

buildRelativePath("app.module.ts", "@scope/package-name")
//returns @scope/package-name

buildRelativePath("app.module.ts", "package-name")
//returns package-name
//should be treated as a package name and not an absolute or relative path unless it starts with `/` or './`
```


this issue is related to angular schematics and located in `@schematics/angular/utility/find-module`

